"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.15.2.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.15.2.2</span> Holy of Holies, Most Holy Place</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">בַּיִת, כַּפֹּרֶת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(beyth hakaporeth)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:11\">1CH 28:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">דְּבִיר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(dvir)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:3\">JOS 10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:38\">JOS 10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:39\">JOS 10:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:21\">JOS 11:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh12:13\">JOS 12:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:7\">JOS 15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:15\">JOS 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:15\">JOS 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:49\">JOS 15:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:15\">JOS 21:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:11\">JDG 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:11\">JDG 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:5\">1KI 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:16\">1KI 6:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:19\">1KI 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:20\">1KI 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:21\">1KI 6:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:22\">1KI 6:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:23\">1KI 6:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:31\">1KI 6:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:49\">1KI 7:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:6\">1KI 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:8\">1KI 8:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:43\">1CH 6:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:16\">2CH 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:20\">2CH 4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:7\">2CH 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:9\">2CH 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:2\">PSA 28:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מִקְדָּשׁ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(miqdash)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:33\">LEV 16:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:3\">EZK 45:3</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">פְּנִימָה, פְּנִימִי</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pnimah, pnimi)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:3\">EZK 41:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:17\">EZK 41:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:17\">EZK 41:17</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">קֹדֶשׁ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(qodesh)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:3\">LEV 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:17\">LEV 16:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:20\">LEV 16:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:23\">LEV 16:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:27\">LEV 16:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:33\">LEV 16:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:21\">EZK 41:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:23\">EZK 41:23</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">קֹדֶשׁ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(qodesh haqodashim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:33\">EXO 26:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:34\">EXO 26:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:16\">1KI 6:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:50\">1KI 7:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:6\">1KI 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:34\">1CH 6:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:8\">2CH 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:10\">2CH 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:22\">2CH 4:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:7\">2CH 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:4\">EZK 41:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ἅγιος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(hagia)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:8\">HEB 9:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12\">HEB 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:25\">HEB 9:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19\">HEB 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:11\">HEB 13:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ἅγιος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(hagia hagiōn)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:3\">HEB 9:3</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ναός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(naos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:5\">REV 15:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc1:10\">3MA 1:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">οἶκος, καταπέτασμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(oikos katapetasmatos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir50:5\">SIR 50:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">σκηνή</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(skēnē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:3\">HEB 9:3</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The Holy of Holies was a cubical room at the west end of the Tabernacle proper and the Temple. In the Tabernacle it measured 10 cubits (5 meters; 16.5 feet) in each direction; in the Temple the dimensions were doubled.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>“Holy of Holies” is a literal translation of the Hebrew expression meaning “most holy of all holy things.” The literal phrase will not be meaningful to most readers. It may be rendered “Most Holy Place” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr>), “second holy room of the Tabernacle/Temple,” or “interior holy room of the Tabernacle/Temple.” What is important here is the degree of holiness, not so much the actual location within the Tabernacle/Temple. It is for this reason that many translators say “most sacred place,” “very, very sacred room,” or “Place/Room that is surpassingly sacred.” In this type of context the term “sacred” may be rendered “dedicated especially to God” or “consecrated to God,” so other possible models for “Holy of Holies” are “room that belongs to God more than any other place” or “room that has been dedicated to God more than any other room.” Another possibility is “Place/Room inside/within the Place where God is.” See also the comments at <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">3.15.2.1 Holy Place&lt;REALIA:3.15.2.1&gt;</a>.</p>\n<p>The inner room of the sanctuary could also be referred to as “within (or, behind) the curtain” (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:2\">LEV 16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:12\">LEV 16:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:15\">LEV 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:7\">NUM 18:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:19\">HEB 6:19</a>; see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">3.14.1.6 Curtain, veil, drape&lt;REALIA:3.14.1.6&gt;</a>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
